						               													<description>Brigandine is a casual open-source skirmish-level fantasy tabletop miniatures rules set. Like many tactical minis wargames, Brigandine uses the I-go-U-go style. The rules are minimalist, and involve very little arithmetic and dice rolling.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Brigandine features:&amp;#10;&amp;#10;- A simple hit resolution system that requires only one die roll per action&amp;#10;- Unit creation rules to allow for any miniatures to be used&amp;#10;- A light, flexible magic system&amp;#10;- A campaign system to link battles in a narrative, and an appendix with an introductory campaign&amp;#10;- No tie to a specific universe or mythos or theme&amp;#10;- 8 sample forces with 40 typical fantasy units generated using the unit creation rules&amp;#10;- An open source license that encourages and forking/redistribution&amp;#10;- Scenarios that work on small (24&amp;quot;x24&amp;quot;) game boards&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Brigandine is licensed under the GNU Free Documentation License.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;</description>
